# Codex Writer Findings — PublicMenu
Chain: publicmenu-260322-125326

## Findings
1. [P1] Pre-checkout loyalty accordion still renders old UI - `x.jsx:1966-1968,3237,3334` still enables `showLoyaltySection`, and `CartView.jsx:902-1034` still renders the full bonus/email/redeem/discount block plus the extra pre-submit loyalty row. This directly conflicts with the batch requirement to remove the pre-checkout loyalty section and replace it with a compact motivational text block above the CTA. FIX: stop rendering the pre-submit loyalty section in `CartView.jsx`; replace it with a small 1-2 line motivational block driven by partner loyalty/discount settings, and keep reward logic only in post-submit surfaces.
2. [P1] Banned "онлайн" wording is still visible in the active checkout flow - `CartView.jsx:1032` shows `Бонусы за онлайн-заказ`, and `x.jsx:3415-3417` shows `По онлайн-заказу вы получите бонусы / скидку`. The task explicitly forbids the word `онлайн` in this dine-in UI because it confuses hall guests. FIX: replace the active pre-submit copy with the new dine-in-safe text variants and remove the old `онлайн` messaging from this flow.
3. [P1] Table confirmation Bottom Sheet is still the old design and still shows a duplicate code field - `x.jsx:3409-3417` keeps the old title/subtitle/benefit copy, `x.jsx:3441-3453` renders a separate visible input with a `0000` placeholder under the visual cells, `x.jsx:3479` keeps `Подтвердить и отправить`, and `x.jsx:3482-3489` keeps `Не тот стол? Изменить`. That preserves the exact confusing UX this batch is supposed to remove. FIX: redesign the sheet to the new IA: title `Введите код стола`, always-visible helper text, four empty cells only, no duplicate field, no change-table link, compact motivation line near the CTA, and button text `Отправить`.
4. [P1] Table verification still auto-submits as soon as the last digit is entered - `CartView.jsx:189-225` calls `verifyTableCode()` automatically on full-length input, while `x.jsx:3466-3475` also exposes a submit button in the Bottom Sheet. In practice the request can fire before the user taps the CTA, so the new button is not authoritative and the redesigned flow cannot behave as specified. FIX: disable the `CartView.jsx` auto-verify effect for the just-in-time Bottom Sheet flow and trigger verification only from the Bottom Sheet submit action after entry is complete.
5. [P1] Motivation text logic is not driven by actual partner configuration - `x.jsx:3415-3417` branches only on `loyaltyEnabled`, so discount-only partners fall back to generic copy, and loyalty partners never see the required dynamic `%` or `+X` values. `CartView.jsx` also has no replacement motivation block at all after removing the old loyalty UI. FIX: derive one source of truth from partner bonus/discount settings and render the four required variants: bonus only, discount only, both, or none.
6. [P2] Cart drawer total still shows the raw cart sum instead of the discounted total - `CartView.jsx:323-326` computes `cartGrandTotal`, but `CartView.jsx:1042` renders `cartTotalAmount`. When discount or redeemed points are active, the amount shown immediately above submit is higher than the amount actually sent. FIX: render `cartGrandTotal` or pass `finalTotal` into the total row so the checkout summary matches the submitted order total.

## Summary
Total: 6 findings (0 P0, 5 P1, 1 P2, 0 P3)

## Prompt Clarity
- Overall clarity: 3
- Ambiguous Fix descriptions (list Fix # and what was unclear): Fix 1 and Fix 2 rely on partner fields described as `or similar`, so the exact source fields for points/discount text were not fully specified from the prompt alone.
- Missing context (what info would have helped): The prompt says `ONLY these 3 files` but names four paths (`CartView.jsx`, `x.jsx`, `README.md`, `BUGS.md`). It also uses `pages/PublicMenu/*.jsx`, which could imply more JSX files than the two named in the task context.
- Scope questions (anything you weren't sure if it's in scope): Whether to treat this as only `CartView.jsx` + `x.jsx` review or every JSX file in `pages/PublicMenu`; whether existing items already listed in `BUGS.md` should be re-reported or only current batch blockers.
